dimension.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In some settings, the entities are blamed for evil in the world. In Bitter Root,
hateful/racist people turn into monsters, and do even worse things. There is a
sense of redeemability in the possessed humans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In other cases, e.g., Outcast and Monstress, humanity is collateral damage in
someone else&amp;rsquo;s war. The entities are refugees on earth, despite being more
powerful than humans.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Potent Word</title><link>https://www.curiosities.dev/tags/potent-word/</link><pubDate>Sun, 12 Feb 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.curiosities.dev/tags/potent-word/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The idea of discourse that has power in and of itself. Can be utilized to create
